            <div class=3D"row mt-5">
                <div class=3D"col-12">
                    <div class=3D"card shadow border-0">
                        <div class=3D"card-header bg-gradient bg-dark text-=
white">
                            <h3 class=3D"card-title mb-0 h5">
                                <i class=3D"fas fa-book me-2"></i>The irreg=
ular octagon: Practical geometry
                            </h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"card-body p-4">
                            <p>
                                The <strong>irregular elongated octagon</st=
rong> is a fascinating example=20
                                of how practical requirements can lead to e=
legant geometric solutions.=20
                                As an octagon with two different side lengt=
hs but uniform interior angles,=20
                                it combines the simplicity of regular forms=
 with the flexibility of irregular=20
                                constructions, finding broad application in=
 technology and design.
                            </p>

                            <h4 style=3D"color: #1565c0;" class=3D"mt-4 mb-=
3">Geometric elegance despite irregularity</h4>
                            <p>
                                The special feature of the elongated octago=
n lies in its structural clarity:
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Uniform angles:</strong> All 8 =
interior angles are exactly 135=C2=B0</li>
                                <li><strong>Two side lengths:</strong> 6 sh=
ort sides (a) and 2 long sides (b)</li>
                                <li><strong>=E2=88=9A2 mathematics:</strong=
> All relationships based on =E2=88=9A2 =E2=89=88 1.414</li>
                                <li><strong>Modular construction:</strong> =
Rectangular middle part with beveled ends</li>
                                <li><strong>Symmetric structure:</strong> H=
orizontally and vertically mirror-symmetric</li>
                                <li><strong>Simple formulas:</strong> Despi=
te irregularity, mathematically manageable</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h4 style=3D"color: #1976d2;" class=3D"mt-4 mb-=
3">The 135=C2=B0 angle: Geometric perfection</h4>
                            <p>
                                The uniform interior angle of 135=C2=B0 mak=
es this octagon special:
                            </p>
                            <div class=3D"row">
                                <div class=3D"col-md-6">
                                    <h6 class=3D"fw-bold text-success">Math=
ematical significance</h6>
                                    <p class=3D"small">135=C2=B0 =3D 90=C2=
=B0 + 45=C2=B0, the perfect combination of right angle and 45=C2=B0 bevel. =
This enables both orthogonal and diagonal construction elements.</p>
                                   =20
                                    <h6 class=3D"fw-bold text-info">Constru=
ctive advantages</h6>
                                    <p class=3D"small">The 135=C2=B0 angle =
allows clean transitions between horizontal/vertical and diagonal elements,=
 ideal for manufacturing and assembly processes.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div class=3D"col-md-6">
                                    <h6 class=3D"fw-bold text-warning">Aest=
hetic harmony</h6>
                                    <p class=3D"small">The 45=C2=B0 bevels =
(exterior angles) create visual dynamism while uniform angles provide calm =
and order.</p>
                                   =20
                                    <h6 class=3D"fw-bold text-danger">Pract=
ical application</h6>
                                    <p class=3D"small">Standard tools and m=
achines can easily execute 45=C2=B0 cuts, simplifying manufacturing and red=
ucing costs.</p>
